items.title: Gavin Newsom Rolls the Dice
items.description: California’s governor hopes that his new gerrymander will help his 2028 presidential prospects.

items.title: A Kennedy Center for the Whole Country?
items.description: With the line between ‘art’ and ‘entertainment’ blurred, Trump’s Kennedy Center seeks to give its audiences a bit of both.

items.title: America Should Celebrate Its Heroes
items.description: The president has rightly recognized the narrow, almost exclusive concentration on victims in our culture of commemoration — and seeks to reverse it.

items.title: Reviving the Presidential Fitness Test Is Worth a Shot
items.description: Critics of Trump’s move seem unable to separate their criticisms from their politics.

items.title: The Left Can’t Stop Self-Destructing
items.description: Democrats are once again denying the obvious, this time about D.C.’s crime problem, to ‘resist’ Trump. But they’re wrong — I should know.
